{"timestamp": "2025-08-04T21:40:18.429429", "elapsed": 0.006048, "ip": "127.0.0.1", "action_type": "request", "player_id": 2, "request": {"endpoint": "/api/v1/daily-quiz", "content_type": "application/json", "content": {"player_answer": "answer2"}}, "response": {"status_code": 200, "content_type": "application/json", "content": {"question": "What is the electric efficiency (i.e., what part of the heat produced is converted to electric power) for a nuclear plant?", "answer1": "25%", "answer2": "35%", "answer3": "45%", "player_answer": "answer2", "correct_answer": "answer2", "answered_correctly": true, "explanation": "The electric efficiency of a nuclear plant is typically around 35%, meaning about 35% of the heat produced by nuclear fission is converted into electric power. The remaining heat is often lost, but it can be utilized for district heating, providing thermal energy for residential and industrial use."}}}
